Cygbuild - A porting tool for making Cygwin net releases
--------------------------------------------------------

Cygbuild is something like Debian dh_make(1) .deb or rpm(1)
.rpm maker utility. It automates package maintenenance so that
with few commands, it is possible to convert a software package
into a installable Cygwin source and binary packages.

    bin/            The programs
    doc/            Documentation
    mk/		    Makefiles; for developers

Important files

    ChangeLog                   Change records
    INSTALL                     Install instructions
    doc/devel/README.txt        Project information. Developer information.
    doc/license/LICENSE.txt     Licensing information
    doc/manual/                 How to use Cygbuild

Project contacts

    Homepage
      http://freecode.net/projects/cygbuild

    Reporting bugs
      See homepage

    Source code repository
      See homepage

Version control information

    Latest development_

        git clone git://git.savannah.nongnu.org/cygbuild.git
        cd cygbuild
        git checkout --track -b devel origin/devel
        make install-etc

    Infrequently released stable:

	git clone git://git.savannah.nongnu.org/cygbuild.git
	cd cygbuild
        git checkout master

    To receive updates (to either one above)

	git pull

End of file
